At the stroke of midnight, something strange and powerful in nature awakens.
The dark night, the moon and the stars hold the secret to a thrilling escape.
The paranormal world is calling, it's up to us to be the light in the dark.

🎨 Materials Needed:
🔹 White paper
🔹 Black paint
🔹 Brush
🔹 Newsprint paper
🔹 Glue
🔹 Scissors
🔸 Optional: a glow in the dark paint pen for added effect

Instructions:

1. Tear sheets of newsprint paper into small, jagged pieces and glue them onto a piece of white paper to create a dark night sky in the background.
2. Using a black paint, paint a moon in the sky. Allow it to dry.
3. With the same black paint, paint small stars all over the background. Allow it to dry.
4. To add a glow in the dark effect, use a glow in the dark paint pen for the moon and stars.
5. Cut out a silhouette of a haunted mansion from black paper.
6. Use a white paint to add creepy details and embellishments to the mansion.
7. Glue the mansion onto the background.
8. Write the title 'Whispers in the Dark' in white paint on a separate piece of paper or cardboard to match the mansion's colour scheme.
9. Glue the title onto the mansion.
10. Showcase the final product in a dramatic manner in the storytime setting.

This project offers a spooky and fun activity that kids will enjoy making.
